    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3aaa91ec_aae1c69c",
        "filename": "monitoring/static/monitoring/js/directives.js",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 127,
      "author": {
        "id": 16168
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T20:48:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Each expression provide comes with chosen metric. Each metric is associated with several dimensions, each having key and value. Match by is a property where you specify those keys. Now since match by is a property of entire alarm definition, I collect all dimension\u0027s keys and mimic set collection to create global match by.\n\nNow assuming expression composed of metrics\n \n metric_1{dim_a\u003d1,dim_b\u003d2}\n metric_2(dim_a\u003d1,dim_c\u003d3}\n metric_3(dim_a\u003d1,dim_d\u003d4}\n\nglobal match by would contain\n \n {dim_a,dim_b,dim_c,dim_d}\n\neffectively allowing to specify one (or all of them).\n\nAs you can see that value is emitted and picked up by match by controller.",
      "parentUuid": "3aaa91ec_4544b748",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 127,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 127,
        "endChar": 50
      },
